properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 13 at 2:04PM CST until January 14 at 6:00AM CST by NWS La Crosse WI
properties.description:
...Another Round of Accumulating Snow Tonight...

.Snow will move into the area this evening, then taper off after
midnight. Plan on snow accumulations tonight of 2 to 4 inches.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation expected. Plan on snow accumulations
of 2 to 4 inches. A light glaze of ice also possible from
freezing drizzle as the snow tapers off.

* WHERE...Portions of central, north central and west central
Wisconsin and southeast Minnesota.

* WHEN...From 7 PM this evening to 6 AM CST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM CST TUESDAY
